<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Inquirer:
</P>
<P>
-- The long-awaited changes in the cabinet of Philippine
President Joseph Estrada crystallized Wednesday with the
irrevocable resignation, effective immediately, of Finance
Secretary Edgardo Espiritu and his four undersecretaries.
</P>
<P>
Business World:
</P>
<P>
-- With a strong agriculture sector, the Philippines' average
annual inflation rate for 1999 was contained at 6.6 percent,
better than the government expectation of between 7 percent and 8
percent,the National Statistics Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Malaya:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippines' overall balance of payments position
remained in a huge surplus of 3.5 billion U.S. dollars based on
the preliminary estimate of the Central Bank of the Philippines as
of December 28 last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
