<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, January 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein on Wednesday
called on Israel and the Palestinians to implement agreements
already signed to achieve a just, durable and comprehensive peace
in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
King Abdullah made the appeal when meeting with an Israeli
delegation headed by Chairman of the Arab Democratic Party in
Israel Abdul Wahab Darawsheh and Israeli Knesset (parliament)
member Talab Sane, Jordan's official news agency Petra said. (
Jordan-Mideast Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Acting Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a
decree Wednesday to appoint Viktor Ivanov as deputy chief of the
presidential administration, said Putin's press service.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov will be in charge of the Kremlin's personnel matters
instead of his predecessor Vladimir Makarov.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Putin relieved Ivanov of his earlier post in
intelligence services. (Russia-Kremlin-Appointment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service
decided Wednesday that a six-year-old boy rescued at sea should be
returned to his father in Cuba by the end of next week.
</P>
<P>
The decision was announced by Doris Meissner, commissioner of
the Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS). The boy, Elian
Gonzalez, should leave Miami and return to Cuba by January 14. (
USA-Cuba-boy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SHEPHERDSTOWN, W. Va. -- The United States said on Wednesday
peace talks between Syria and Israel were "chugging along" after
working groups started their technical discussions over major
issues existing between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We are chugging along in a professional manner," the State
Department spokesman James Rubin told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Experts from Syria, Israel and the United States formed four
committees on Wednesday and two of them convened right after the
setting up of the committees. They were the committees on peace
term and on security. The other two tackling Israel's withdrawal
from the Golan Heights and water sharing will be convened within
the week but not on Wednesday. (Syria-Isreal-Talks) 
</P>
</TEXT>
