<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stocks Exchange
on Wednesday closed higher with the benchmark IPC index increasing
by 89.04 points, or 1.33 percent, at 6,764 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 114.9 million shares worth some 266.4
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the Mexican peso, stood at 9.70 to one
dollar for sale and 9.35 for purchase from the National Bank of
Mexico (Banamex). 
</P>
</TEXT>
