<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lewis Sets Fight Against Grant in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Lennox Lewis has agreed
Wednesday to defend his undisputed heavyweight championship
against Michael Grant on April 29, a spokesman for his U.S.
promoter Main Events said.
</P>
<P>
Although the site for Lewis' first defence of the title he won
by beating Evander Holyfield in November has not been set, it
likely will be Madison Square Garden, said Donald Tremblay, a
spokesman for Main Events.
</P>
<P>
Lewis will receive about 10 million U.S. dollars and Grant 3-4
million U.S. dollars for the bout to be broadcast by TVKO, HBO's
pay-per-view arm.
</P>
<P>
The 1.98 meter tall Lewis holds a 35-1-1 record while the 2.01
meter tall Grant is 31-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
