<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Beats Al Nassr 3-1 in World Club Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Real Madrid of Spain
defeated Saudi Arabia side Al Nassr 3-1 in the opening match of
the World Club Soccer Championship in Sao Paulo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Nicolas Anelka scored the opening goal in the 21st
minute. The Saudis levelled the score from a penalty converted by
Fahad Al Husseini in first half injury time.
</P>
<P>
Goalkeeper Mohammed Babkr of Al Nassr attempted to punch away
an innocuous cross by Geremi Njitap but instead diverted the ball
into his own goal, where Raul provided the finishing touch.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes later, Savio netted Real's third goal from a
penalty after Anelka, leaping on another defensive blunder, was
bundled over in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
