<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Timken Increases Presence in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Timken Company, one of the
world's leading bearings manufacturers, is set to increase its
interest in a joint venture with the Yantai Bearings Plant in the
coastal city of Yantai in east China's Shandong Province, and turn
it into one of Asia's major bearings production centers.
</P>
<P>
To accomplish this, a Timken source said, that his company will
further increase investment in Yantai Timken Co., Ltd. in the
years to come.
</P>
<P>
"We have full confidence in our development in this country,"
the source said.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, Timken has already increased its
investment in Yantai Timken to 10 million U.S. dollars since the
joint venture was established in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The venture now provides bearings to such major automobile
producers as Shanghai Volkswagen and the China No.1 Automobile
Group Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Timken has operations in 25 countries and regions around the
world with annual sales amounting to 2.7 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
