<HEADLINE> East China Province to Enhance Cooperation with Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province,
one of the country's economic powerhouses, will enhance
cooperation with Macao to promote common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Chen Huanyou, secretary of the Jiangsu Provincial Committee of
the Communist Party of China, said that Macao's return to China on
December 20, 1999 provides many opportunities for further
cooperation between his province and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Greater efforts will be made to boost cooperation and exchanges
between the two sides in economic, trade, educational, scientific
and technological fields, Chen said. Jiangsu expects to do more
business with Europe through Macao, as Macao has maintained close
ties with European countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Cooperative projects will be launched in scientific research,
higher education and management, and information networks linking
the two sides will be improved to meet the needs of increasing
cooperation in various fields, according to Chen.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has opened nearly all sectors of its economy to the
outside world, and foreign trade accounts for one-fourth of its
GDP, while foreign capital makes up one-fourth of its total
spending on fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
The province has also maintained an annual growth of 12.6
percent on average over the past two decades, with the GDP
reaching 720 billion yuan in 1998, ranking second in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
