<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Expects to Draw More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
expects to attract more foreign funds this year, and is
encouraging foreign investors to develop its service industry.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, the province received 3.3
billion US dollars of contractual foreign investment in 1999, up
10 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Shandong expects foreign groups to invest in retail sale
projects and foreign-funded banks in Jinan, and in the insurance
business in the cities of Qingdao and Jinan, said Wang Chuntao,
director of the provincial department of foreign trade and
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The director also hopes that state approve the establishment of
foreign-funded travel agencies in Shandong.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to have agents in Europe, America, Japan,
and the Republic of Korea to help the province attract more
investment, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
