<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wenger Struggles to Keep Kanu on FA Cup Trial  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer
club Arsenal mananger Arsene Wenger has refused to abandon hope of
losing Kanu from this weekend's FA Cup fourth round tie.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal are still locked in talks with the player's agents and
Nigerian coach Amodu Shaibu, who has threatened to invoke FIFA
sanctions to get the Gunners kicked out of the FA Cup if Kanu isn'
t released on time.
</P>
<P>
FIFA rules state Kanu should join his Nigeria team-mates on
Sunday to prepare for the African Nations Cup but the Londoners
want him to play in the FA Cup tie with Leicester on the same day.
</P>
<P>
An Arsenal spokesman said: "We are pursuing the possibility of
Kanu playing in Sunday's FA Cup clash with Leicester and are
currently trying to resolve the matter with the relevant parties."
</P>
<P>
Nigerian coach Shaibu hit out at Wenger's delaying tactics but
the parties are still involved in a series of talks about when the
player will leave Highbury.
</P>
<P>
Shaibu has even threatened to invoke FIFA's 14-day rule which
governs clubs releasing players for major tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Shaibu said: "If Arsenal play Kanu in the FA Cup we will invoke
FIFA sanctions against them. If it was a league game they would
lose the points, so if it's a cup tie they must lose the tie."
</P>
<P>
FIFA regulations state that all players should be available 14
days before a major tournament starts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
