<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Cabinet to Set Up Human Rights Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's government
Wednesday decided to set up a sub-committee on human rights under
the cabinet, the state-run Associated Press of Pakistan reported.
</P>
<P>
The National Security Council and the federal cabinet of
Pakistan, which met Wednesday under the chairmanship of Chief
Executive General Pervaiz Musharraf here, made this decision, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
The sub-committee will be headed by Federal Minister for Law
and Justice Aziz A. Munshi and it will make recommendations to the
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Earlier the joint meeting had discussed a report by the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs on human rights issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
