<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 20 Injured in Road Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- At least three persons were killed
and 20 others injured Wednesday in a road accident at Bharadoba on
the Dhaka-Mymensingh highway, about 60 kilometers north of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Wednesday night said the accident
occurred when a Dhaka-bound private car collided head-on with a
passenger bus coming from the opposite direction.
</P>
<P>
One person died on the spot and an unidentified woman and a
child succumbed to injuries at a hospital after admission.
</P>
</TEXT>
