<HEADLINE> Liaoning Snaps Beijing Home Winning Streak in CBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Hunters edged Beijing
Ducks on Wednesday 71-69 to snap Beijing's ninth straight home
winning streak at the Chinese Basketball Association league.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning, who beat Beijing 82-79 in their first meet on
November 28 last year at home, promoted to third place in the team
standings with a 9-5 record.
</P>
<P>
In Nanjing, Dedending champions Bayi Rockets became the only
team to keep home win as they overcame a 53-57 halftime trail to
trounce Jiangsu Dragons 123-98 in a road game. Bayi now is 14-1
including eight home wins.
</P>
<P>
In Jinan, Shandong Bulls avenged their last defeat to nip
Vanguard Aoshen 103-93 at home, giving their veteran coach Ye Nan
a second straight win since he replaced his former position Ma
Lianmin.
</P>
<P>
Shandong lost to Vanguard Aoshen 90-100 in their last meet last
month in Jingjiang, Fujian Province. Now Bulls is fourth in the
standing at an identical record 8-6 with Beijing and Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
In Shanghai, Guangdong Hongyuan surprised Shanghai Sharks 92-87,
reseating its second place chair of the league with a 10-4 record.
While Shanghai (9-5) shares third spot with liaoning.
</P>
<P>
In Changchun, Jilin Northeast Tigers downed Hubei Mei'erya 102-
91, while Zhejing Cyclone beat Nanjing Army 112-95 in Hangzhou.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
