<HEADLINE> Iranian National Team Leaves for U.S.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian national team left here
on Wednesday for the United States to play in three preparatory
matches after the U.S. Football Federation promised to waive
finger printing procedure.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for the Iranian national football
team to visit the U.S. since the 1979 Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
President of the Iranian National Football Federation Mohsen
Safaeie Farahani, who headed a 9-man delegation, is accompanying
the Iranian team, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The 21-man Iranian team will have a 7-hour stopover in
Frankfort, Germany in order to obtain U.S. visas before leaving
the German city for Chicago, the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian team will first play against the Mexican national
team at the Oakland stadium on Monday and then face the Ecuadorian
national team in Los Angeles on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It will finally play against the U.S. national team at the Rose
Ball stadium in Pasadena on January 17, the report said.  
</P>
