<HEADLINE> Cold Wave Increases Sufferings of Bangladeshis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- A blinding fog and a moderate cold
wave that gripped different parts of Bangladesh have caused
serious difficulties to the communications system and increased
sufferings of the poor, the official Bangladesh News Agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Northern districts of the country have been experiencing a
moderate cold wave since the beginning of this month. More than
nine deaths have so far been reported in the prevailing cold wave
in the northern region.
</P>
<P>
Inter-district transports including buses, lorries, trains,
launches and low-altitude domestic flights have faced difficulties
in their normal operation mainly due to dense fog, which reduced
visibility to less than four meters.
</P>
<P>
According to weather experts, in the next 24 hours thick fog
may occur over the western parts of the country while a slight
fall in night temperatures is expected in the Dhaka division.
</P>
</TEXT>
