<HEADLINE> Swearing-in of Reelected Mozambican President Set on January 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The swearing-in of incumbent
President Joaquim Chissano for another five-year term will take
place on January 15, the Mozambican Supreme Court said in a note
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the note, Chissano will be sworn into office by
President of the Supreme Court, Mario Mangaze, at a public
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The National Elections Committee on December 22 announced that
Chissano beat his sole rival Afonso Dhlakama by winning 52.29
percent of the votes in the December 3-5 elections.
</P>
<P>
Dhlakama, leader of the opposition Mozambican National
Resistance (Renamo), renewed his demand for a recount of the poll
results despite the Supreme Court's ruling that validated the
announced results.
</P>
<P>
Renamo Thursday confirmed that it will boycott the opening
session of the country's newly-elected parliament, the Assembly of
the Republic, scheduled for January 14.
</P>
<P>
Renamo General-secretary Joao Alexandre told Radio Mozambique
that the 117 deputies from Renamo and its allies in the "Electoral
Union" will not take their seats in the assembly. The "Electoral
Union" consists of Renamo plus 10 minor parties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the coalition is waiting for a dialog with the
ruling Mozambique Liberation Front Party (Frelimo) "in order to
achieve a platform of understanding. "
</P>
<P>
But President Chissano and Frelimo General Secretary Manuel
Tome have made it clear that the country cannot grind to a halt
just because Renamo disagrees with the Supreme Court's ruling.
</P>
<P>
They held that the Frelimo deputies will take their seats and
parliamentary business will start with or without Renamo's
presence.
</P>
<P>
The assembly can function without Renamo since Frelimo holds
133 of the 250 seats, exceeding the quorum of 126 (50 percent plus
one).
</P>
<P>
However, it is not clear whether Renamo will be able to oblige
all its coalition partners to adhere to the boycott. 
</P>
</TEXT>
