<HEADLINE> Switzerland's Sunrise Sharply Lowers Phone Call Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the occasion of its second anniversary, Sunrise announced
that it is cutting charges by as much as 74 percent, with a
telephone call within Switzerland now costing a maximum ten
centimes (about 0.7 U.S. dollar per minute.
</P>
<P>
To simplify the tariff structure, from January 1, 2000, Sunrise
users are able to make phone calls to European Union countries as
well as to America and Canada at one single rate around the clock.
</P>
<P>
The price war has been heating up since January 1998 when the
Swiss market was liberalized and the then state-owned Swiss
Telecom (now Swisscom) lost its monopoly.
</P>
<P>
A number of companies including Sunrise, Orange and Diax have
launched major publicity campaigns and dangled the bait of lower
charges to attract customers. 
