"The Secretary-General has announced today the appointment," and "
Turk will be replacing Mr. Alvaro de Soto, who has been appointed
by the Secretary-General as his Special Advisor on Cyprus, and who
will be taking up an appointment as Special Representative of the
Secretary-General for Cyprus in the spring of this year."
</P>
<P>
"Turk is expected to come on board at the beginning of February,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
Turk, born in February 1952, became the Slovenian permanent
representative to the United Nations in September 1992. His
country was the non-permanent member of the Security Council in
1998 and 1999.
</P>
<P>
Turk was chairman of the Working Group of the Third Committee
of the General Assembly on reform of U.N. mechanisms in the field
of Human Rights from 1994 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
Turk was also chairman of the Security Council's committee on
sanctions against Libya, set up under the Security Council
resolution 748 in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Turk's involvement with the United Nations began in 1981, when
he was elected vice-chairman of the Working Group of the Right to
Development, a post he held until 1984. 
