<HEADLINE> Netherlands, S.Africa Cooperate on Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands and South
Africa are ready to cooperate in the field of transport and
infrastructure development, the Dutch government said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The government said in a news release that a protocol to this
effect was signed in The Hague Wednesday. The plans will be worked
out in more detail in April at the first meeting of the South
Africa-Netherlands Transport Forum.
</P>
<P>
Among other things, the cooperation with the South African port
authority PortNet will be fleshed out further, the government said.
</P>
<P>
A Traffic Safety working group will focus on the available
Dutch expertise in the area of bus transport safety, following a
number of serious bus accidents in recent months, it added.
</P>
</TEXT>
