<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Currency Depreciates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's currency, birr,
has been depreciating against the U.S. dollar in the past year.
</P>
<P>
The birr's exchange rate was fixed at a normal rate of 8.14 to
one U.S. dollar on January 1, from 7.5 birr to on dollar at the
end of 1998
</P>
<P>
The birr stood for nearly three decades at a fixed exchange
rate of 2.07 to one dollar.
</P>
<P>
The continued depreciation was attributed to the downward trend
on the prices of coffee and hides and skins -- Ethiopia's two main
foreign exchange earners. 
</P>
