<HEADLINE> Irish Court Hears IRA Extradition Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Angelo Fusco, 43, was at the center of an extraordinary legal
tangle earlier this week after he was arrested by police in County
Kerry, south-west Ireland, the Reuters reported.
</P>
<P>
A police convoy carrying Fusco to the border with British-ruled
Northern Ireland was stopped on Tuesday when Irish High Court
judge Joseph Finnegan blocked the extradition. He ordered Fusco to
appear before the court in Dublin on Thursday.
</P>
