<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa Enters to Final of Hopman Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- American James Blake defeated
Wayne Ferreira 6-4,6-4 but could not stop South Africa in the
final of the Hopman Cup teams tennis tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Blake, ranked 219, looked sharp as he struck winners from all
angles, while Ferreira failed to connect with his returns and paid
the price for a succession of careless errors.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Amanda Coetzer had taken just 59 minutes to dismiss
Alexandra Stevenson 6-3, 6-1, and the United States then claimed
the doubles 6-7 (5-7), 6-3, 6-2 to give the Americans a 2-1
victory.
</P>
<P>
Thailand also kept its hopes alive of advancing from
qualifying to Saturday's final when it defeated Slovakia 3-0 as
Paradorn Srichaphan surprised 17th-ranked Karol Kucera 4-6, 7-6 (7-
2), 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Tamarine Tanasugarn outlasted Henrieta Nagyova 2-6, 6-2, 4-1
to give Thailand a winning start against Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Srichiphan then scored the biggest victory of his career when
he dismissed Kucera, taking advantage of the Slovakian's 17 double-
faults while firing his ninth ace on match point.
</P>
<P>
Because of Nagyova's injury, Slovakia defaulted the mixed
doubles, giving Thailand a 3-0 victory.
</P>
<P>
In another late match Thursday, Sweden beat Belgium 2-1.
</P>
</TEXT>
