<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Southern Bank to Acquire United Merchant Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Southern Bank
Bhd Thursday entered into an agreement with United Merchant Group
Bhd (UMG) to acquire the latter's equity interest in United
Merchant Finance Bhd (UMF).
</P>
<P>
The Southern Bank, one of the leading banks in Malaysia, said
in a statement that it will acquire UMG's equity in UMF for 319.
415 million ringgit (84.056 million U.S. dollars) in cash,
representing 1.2 times the adjusted net tangible assets of UMF as
on June 30, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The price takes into account UMF's future earnings potential
while the adjustments are based on Bank Negara (State Bank)
Malaysia's guidelines and other parameters as agreed upon by the
Southern Bank and UMG, it said.
</P>
<P>
The purchase consideration shall be subject to adjustments to
account for any changes to the net tangible asset of UMF during
the
financial period commencing on July 1, 1999, up to the month-end
immediately preceding completion of the proposed acquisition, the
Southern Bank said.
</P>
<P>
The proposed acquisition will be funded initially with
borrowings of the Southern Bank group, it said.
</P>
<P>
Describing the deal as a significant milestone for the bank,
the Southern Bank's Chief Executive Director T. H. Tan said in a
statement that the UMF acquisition was earnings positive and that
would provide an entree into the attractive mortgage, hire
purchase and leasing markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
