<HEADLINE> Pakistan Gifts Wheat, Medicines to Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Thursday dispatched 5,
000 metric tons of wheat, flour and medicines worth 10 million
rupees (192,000 U.S. dollars) to Afghanistan on the occasion of
Eid-ul-Fitr, a Muslim festival.
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Office spokesman said in a statement that the food
situation in Afghanistan has been a cause of great concern. "The
government of Pakistan has been periodically offering humanitarian
assistance to the government and people of Afghanistan," it said.
</P>
<P>
As part of this humanitarian assistance, a consignment
comprising 11 trucks of flour and one truck of medicines was
dispatched to Kabul Thursday, the statement said. 
