<HEADLINE> Parents, Sister of Wednesday's Bomber Arrested in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The parents and the sister of
the woman suicide bomber who exploded herself in front of the
Prime Minister's Office were arrested Thursday in the east of Sri
Lanka, official radio said Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The suicide bomber killed 13 people and wounded more than 20
others in front of the Sri Lankan Prime Minister's Office in
central Colombo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was not in her office at the time of the
explosion. Police suspect that Tamil rebels were behind the blast.
</P>
<P>
A senior police officer was quoted as saying the bomber's
parents and sister were arrested Thursday morning by the Special
Task Force in Akkaraipattu in Eastern Province of the country.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the mother is a Sinhalese and the bomber
joined the Tamil rebels about one and half years ago, the radio
added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate Tamil state in the north and
east of Sri Lanka.
</P>
</TEXT>
