<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Injured in Train Blast in Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people were
injured in a bomb blast in a train at the Old Delhi railway
station Thursday afternoon, police said.
</P>
<P>
The medium-intensity explosion took place in a compartment of
an express immediately after it reached the platform from the yard,
Deputy Commissioner of Police P.K. Srivastava said.
</P>
<P>
The blast shattered the window panes, ripped apart all the
seats and created a one-meter radius hole in the bogie, he said.
</P>
<P>
The train was for Saharanpur in the north state of Uttar
Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
He said the bomb might have been kept under a seat in one of
the second-class compartments.
</P>
<P>
A team from the Central Forensic Sciences Laboratory had
reached the spot to determine the nature of the explosive used in
the blast while a sniffer dog squad had also been pressed into
service to examine the spot, the Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The entire area has been cordoned off by the police and a large
number of personnel have been deployed at the station. And
movement of people at all entry and exit points was being strictly
monitored.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the railway station said some trains had been
rescheduled due to the blast.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the blast at the Old Delhi station, the police
control room here received a call which said a bomb had also been
planted somewhere at the New Delhi railway station, police sources
said.
</P>
<P>
A team from the local police station is making thorough checks
and vans from the police have also been rushed to the spot though
police said the call seemed to be a hoax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
