<HEADLINE> India Sets Up Fund for Scientific Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government Thursday
set up a fund for the improvement of the science and technology
infrastructure in universities and other higher education
institutions.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the establishment of the fund at his residence,
Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee said it would improve the
inadequate infrastructure for basic research in higher education
institutions in the country.
</P>
<P>
Saying basic research is the mother of all technologies,
Vajpayee expressed dismay at the decline of bright students
choosing to pursue scientific research in the country.
</P>
<P>
This was probably because they were being attracted by several
other lucrative career options, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The lack of a conducive atmosphere and opportunities for
conducting high-quality research on a sustained basis is also a
reason" for the dwindling of students in scientific research, the
prime minister admitted.
</P>
<P>
The Indian leader asked young scientists to aim higher and work
with "redoubled dedication" to meet the expectations of the people.
</P>
<P>
Vajpayee also issued five-year fellowships of 25,000 rupees (
some 580 U.S. dollars) per month to six young scientists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
