<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Airlines Targets 2.6 Million Passengers in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 6 (Xinhua ) -- Vietnam Airlines has set a target
of transporting 2,585,000 passengers and more than 40,000 tons of
cargo this year, Vietnam News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Vietnam Airlines carried 2.56 million passengers and
41,000 tons of cargo, up by 5 and 8 percent respectively, over the
figures recorded in 1998.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the corporation also conducted special flights to
Scandinavian and African countries, Cuba, India, Japan, Australia
and New Zealand last year.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1999, Vietnam Airlines coordinated with domestic and
foreign tourism agencies to launch promotional campaigns.
</P>
<P>
At present, Vietnam Airlines operates 49 air routes to 15
domestic and 16 foreign destinations, either directly or through
cooperation with foreign airlines such as Malaysia Airlines,
Singapore Airlines, Japan Airlines, Korean Air, Lao Aviation, Air
France and Swiss Air.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's national flag carrier also plans to open direct air
routes linking Ho Chi Minh City and Cambodia's Siemreap province,
Hanoi and China's Kunming city, and Hanoi and Seoul of the
Republic of Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
