<HEADLINE> U.N. Urged to Give More Aid for Angolan Refugees in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's North Western Province
Thursday called on the United Nations to give more materials and
logistic support to Angolan refugees in the province bordering
Angola.
</P>
<P>
Permanent Secretary of the province Maybin Mubanga also urged
the Zambian government to transfer Angolan soldiers in Mwinilunga
and Solwezi of the province to a refugees camp in Mongu of
neighboring West Province.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers cannot be left along the borders as they are not
civilians, the Zambia News Agency quoted Mubanga as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said it is difficult to monitor over 36,000 refugees
currently in his province and more tents for shelter are needed at
the established transit centers.
</P>
<P>
Mubanga said there is also a critical shortage of fuel, making
it impossible for security personnel to carry out patrols around
the borders.
</P>
<P>
The official called on the Zambian government to ensure that
there is adequate supply of fuel to his province. 
</P>
