<HEADLINE> CPC Provincial Committee Leaders Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) has appointed some new leaders of
the provincial committees of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Hui Liangyu has been moved from the post as secretary of the
CPC Anhui Provincial Committee, member of the Standing Committee
of the CPC Anhui Provincial Committee, and member of the CPC Anhui
Provincial Committee to his new post as secretary of the CPC
Jiangsu Provincial Committee, member of the Standing Committee of
the CPC Jiangsu Provincial Committee and member of the CPC Jiangsu
Provincial Committee.
</P>
<P>
Wang Taihua has been appointed secretary of the CPC Anhui
Provincial Committee. Xu Zhonglin has become vice-secretary of the
CPC Anhui Provincial Committee, member of the Standing Committee
of the CPC Anhui Provincial Committee, and member of the CPC Anhui
Provincial Committee from his former position as vice-secretary of
the CPC Jiangsu Provincial Committee, member of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Jiangsu Provincial Committee and member of
the CPC Jiangsu Provincial Committee.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yongkang has been appointed secretary of the CPC Sichuan
Provincial Committee, member of the Standing Committee of the CPC
Sichuan Provincial Committee and member of the CPC Sichuan
Provincial Committee.
</P>
<P>
Song Fatang has been moved from vice-secretary of the CPC
Shandong Provincial Committee, member of the Standing Committee of
the CPC Shandong Provincial Committee and member of the CPC
Shandong Provincial Committee to become vice-secretary of the CPC
Heilongjiang Provincial Committee, member of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Heilongjiang Provincial Committee and member
of the CPC Heilongjiang Provincial Committee.
</P>
<P>
Also appointed to new positions were Chen Huanyou, former
secretary of the CPC Jiangsu Provincial Committee and former
member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Jiangsu Provincial
Committee, Xie Shijie, former secretary of the CPC Sichuan
Provincial Committee and former member of the Standing Committee
of the CPC Sichuan Provincial Committee, and Tian Fengshan, former
vice-secretary of the CPC Heilongjiang Provincial Committee and
former member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Heilongjiang
Provincial Committee.  
