<HEADLINE> Editorial: Take Every Opportunity in the New Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China should take every
opportunity to accelerate economic growth, according to an
editorial to be published tomorrow in the "People's Daily".
</P>
<P>
The editorial, entitled "Take Every Opportunity and Forge Ahead
", calls on the people to make further efforts to build a stronger
China in the new centuary.
</P>
<P>
Changes in the global economy and science and technology will
help China introduce more capital, technology and management
experience from abroad while playing a more active role in the
world market, it says.
</P>
<P>
In the past 50 years, China has made great achievements in
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, it adds.
</P>
<P>
To take opportunities in the new century, China needs to be
more enterprising and explorative, according to the editorial. The
country should also be innovative and flexible in the course of
reform and development, it adds.
</P>
<P>
The editorial notes that China will do all it can to overcome
present difficulties and should fully exploit its favorable
political and economic situation as it forges a brighter future.
</P>
