<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Key Falun Gong Cult Members Sentenced in Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Two key members of the banned
Falun Gong Cult were sentenced to prison today by the Wuhan
Intermediate People's Court.
</P>
<P>
Xu Xianglan, the leader of the Falun Gong headquarters in
Wuhan and her husband Wang Hansheng were sentenced to eight and
six years imprisonment respectively. They were charged with
organizing and using the cult to obstruct justice.
</P>
<P>
The court, which was open to the public today, revealed that
Xu began to practise Falun Gong in 1992 and soon become a Falun
Gong instructor in Wuhan. She had colluded with Falun Gong leader
Li Hongzhi in setting up the Falun Gong Wuhan headquarters and
published a periodical to publicize the teachings and activities
of the Cult.
</P>
<P>
During June 6-8, 1998, Xu organized, on nine occasions, Falun
Gong practitioners to besiege the general office of "Changjiang
Daily Newspaper", seriously disrupting the public order and the
stability of the city.
</P>
<P>
From May 1996 to May 1999, Xu and her husband also illegally
published Falun Gong promotional materials, raking in a total of
10.31 million yuan (1.25 million US dollars) in illegal profit.
</P>
<P>
She also took a leading role in spreading the cult in Hubei,
Hunan, Jiangxi, Zhejiang and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Xu was the principal criminal with her husband as accessory.
They should be punished by law accordingly, the court said.
</P>
<P>
However, since Xu and Wang confessed to their crimes and showed
some repentance by revealing the true nature of the Falun Gong
Cult, the court showed leniency in their sentences.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
