<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Sharply Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks plunged 693.
49 points, or 4.38 percent, to close at 15,153.23 Thursday after
posting the biggest point drop since late 1997 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Traders and analysts said they thought the selling was overdone,
with much of the latest wave of selling believed to be retail-led,
with some investors hit by margin calls.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 23.113 billion HK dollars (2.963 billion U.S.
dollars), 1.635 billion HK dollars (210 million U.S. dollars) less
than Wednesday's 24.747 billion HK dollars (3.173 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the four sub-indices suffered decreases, with Finances,
Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry losing 3.25 percent,
0.93 percent, 4.32 percent and 5.30 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 2.68 percent and Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index down 0.78 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks rose 95.35 points, or 0.60 percent, to open at
15,942.07 Wednesday and plunged 531.81 points, or 3.36 percent, to
close the morning session at 15,314.91. 
</P>
</TEXT>
