<HEADLINE> Taiwan Compatriots Greet New Year in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 250 Taiwan compatriots
gathered in a New Year get-together in Hong Kong Thursday to greet
the upcoming Year of the Dragon of the lunar calendar.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech, Zou Zhekai, deputy director of the Xinhua
News Agency Hong Kong Branch, said the development of the cross-
Straits relations is an issue of common concern and closely
related to the interests of people on both sides of the Taiwan
Straits at the start of the century.
</P>
<P>
After the return of Hong Kong and Macao, to settle the Taiwan
question and realize the reunification of the motherland has
become a more prominent task for the Chinese people, Zou said.
</P>
<P>
He praised the people in various circles of Hong Kong and
Taiwan compatriots living in the region for their effort in the
past year to promote the cross-Straits relations and their
patriotism.
</P>
<P>
Besides economic, cultural and personnel exchanges between Hong
Kong and Taiwan, Hong Kong compatriots also offered help to the
rescue work following the September 21 earthquake in Taiwan, he
said, noting that this shows that blood is thicker than water.
</P>
<P>
Zou expressed the hope that the Hong Kong people from all walks
of life and Taiwan compatriots in Hong Kong will unite and make
joint efforts to promote the peaceful reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Attending the get-together were also Jiang Enzhu, director of
the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, and leading officials of
the Taiwan Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong and the Chinese
General Chamber of Commerce of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
