<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's External Trade Increases in October 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The volume of total exports of
Hong Kong registered a year-on-year increase of 9.2 percent in
October 1999, while the volume of imports rose by 8.0 percent,
according to the Census and Statistics Department Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Of the export figure, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports
increased by 11.9 percent over a year earlier, while that of
domestic exports fell by 9.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first 10 months of 1999 with the same period of
the previous year, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports grew by 3.
4 percent, while the volume of domestic exports dropped by 9.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, the volume of total exports increased by 1.6
percent and the imports fell by 2.5 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing October 1999 with the year-ago period, the prices of
re-exports and domestic exports fell by 1.4 percent and 1.9
percent respectively. Import prices also declined by 0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
As regards price changes in the first 10 months of 1999 over
the previous corresponding period, the prices of re-exports and
domestic exports were down by 3.2 percent and 2.6 percent
respectively, and import prices by 2.6 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
