<HEADLINE> Philippine House Speaker Pushes Benefits for Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippine House Speaker Manuel
Villar said Thursday that he wants better wages and benefits for
the country's thousands of public school teachers.
</P>
<P>
Villar said in a radio interview that legislation that will
provide long-term benefits for the country's educators is being
drawn up in the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
"This is necessary in uplifting the lives of our teachers and
improving the country's quality of education," he said.
</P>
<P>
Two separate bills seeking to grant added benefits and mid-year
bonus to teachers are also being discussed by the House Committee
on Basic Education, said Villar.
</P>
<P>
"As much as possible, we are looking for ways to source funds
to increase the salary of government workers," he said.
</P>
<P>
Villar also stressed that he supports the planned 10-percent
salary increase this year for government employees as promised by
President Joseph Estrada. "This will be a big help to them," said
Villar.
</P>
<P>
The country's teachers, he said, are vital components in the
proper education of Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
"They will be the ones to mold the minds of the young so we
should make sure that we take good care of them and that we are
able to attract the best educators into the profession," Villar
said.
</P>
<P>
Public school teachers, he said, have long been neglected and
many of their needs, mostly financial, have not been properly
addressed due to the government's lack of resources. "We are doing
what we can to help them," he added.
</P>
<P>
Under Villar's leadership, the House of Representatives has
passed vital measures to address the plights of the "neglected
sectors" which include the disabled, war veterans, the elderly,
women and children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
