<HEADLINE> 350,000 Rwandans Die of AIDS-Related Diseases in 1999: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- About 350,000 Rwandans died of
HIV/AIDS- related diseases, the Rwanda News Agency quoted a senior
official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Some 150,000 adults and over 200,000 children died of such kind
of diseases last year alone, said Ntaganira Innocent, director of
Rwandan National AIDS control program.
</P>
<P>
He added that 60,000 children were orphaned due to HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
However, the AIDS expert noted that better statistics will be
provided in February this year after study results have been fully
compiled.
</P>
<P>
According to the director, 60 percent of patients in Rwandan
hospitals have AIDS-related ailments and over 400,000 people have
been infected by HIV, the virus that causes AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Anyway, Ntaganira expressed satisfaction with the actual
achievements in combating AIDS pandemic in the country for the
past year. He did not elaborate the achievements.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan government has for the first time allocated 100
million Rwandan francs (one U.S. dollar equals some 380 Rwandan
francs) as part of this year's recurrent budget to finance its
efforts in fighting AIDS scourge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
