<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Urges Cote d'Ivoire to Clarify Declaration on Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- France called on Cote d'Ivoire on
Thursday to clarify its declaration that it would suspend the
payment of all foreign debts.
</P>
<P>
Assistant spokesman of the French Foreign Ministry Francois
Rivasseau said that France has no "precisions" on the annoucement
made by Cote d'Ivoire's new strongman, General Robert Guei, that
payment of foreign debts had been suspended.
</P>
<P>
"It is important that Cote d'Ivoire continues to honor its
financial commitment," he said.
</P>
<P>
In a speech made to the transitional government on Wednesday,
Guei said that the "chests (of the state) are totally empty."
</P>
<P>
He said that it was with "the strength of 1,000 gymnasts" that
the government has just paid its employees and that all this was
made possible by a suspension of payment of foreign debts.
</P>
<P>
Cote d'Ivoire owes international creditors about 93 billion
francs (16 billion U.S. dollars) of debts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
