<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Sees Current Account Surplus in Third Quarter of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The 15-nation European Union (
EU) recorded a surplus of 3.4 billion euros (3.5 billion U.S.
dollars for the third quarter of 1999, Eurostat, the EU
statistical office, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is a newly revised figure, as compared with a surplus of
13.3 billion European currency units (ECUs, some 14.3 U.S. billion
dollars) in the same period of 1998, and a surplus of 10 billion
euros (10.3 billion U.S. dollars) in the second quarter of 1999.
</P>
<P>
In the third quarter of 1999, Eurostat said, the 15-country
bloc's external balance of trade in services showed a slight
deficit - 9 million euros (9.3 million U.S. dollars) -- compared
with a surplus of 1.5 billion ECUs (1.6 billion U.S. dollars) in
the third quarter of 1998 and with a surplus of 2.7 billion euros
(2.9 billion U.S. dollars) in the second quarter of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
