<HEADLINE> Martinez Rolls into Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Former Wimbledon champion
Conchita Martinez Thursday secured a semifinal berth at the
Australian women's hardcourt tennis championships held in Gold
Coast, Australia, by beating Sabine Appelmans of Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard, third-seeded who overcame a poor serving
throughout her quarterfinal win over eighth-seeded Appelmans7-6 (7-
3), 4-6, 6-4, joined Croatian Silvija Talaja in the last four at
the event.
</P>
<P>
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain, the fourth seed, joined
Martinez in the semifinals when she beat fifth-seeded Patty
Schnyder of Switzerland 2-6, 7-6 (7-2), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Nathalie Dechy of France, the sixth seed, defeated Magdalena
Maleeva of Bulgaria 6-4, 6-7 (2-7), 7-6 (8-6) in another
quarterfinal. Talaja beat second seed Anna Kournikova in their
quarterfinal on Wednesday.  
</P>
