<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway's Bakke Jumps atop Standings in World Cup Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Norway's Trine Bakke skied to
two perfect runs Thursday to take her first slalom World Cup
victory of the season in Maribor, and jumped atop the standings.
</P>
<P>
Bakke took advantage of her No. 1 starting in the first run,
posting the fastest time of 51.75 seconds and a lead of 42
hundredths of a second.
</P>
<P>
Starting 30th in the second run, Bakke was undisturbed by the
rougher course and again had the fastest time, finishing with an
aggregate of 1 minute, 41.90 seconds, and a victory by .87.
</P>
<P>
Slovenian Spela Pretnar, who was cheered wildly by thousands
of local fans, finished second in 1:42.77. Austrian Sabine Egger
was third in 1:42.99.
</P>
<P>
The victory pushed Bakke atop lead in World Cup slalom
standings past 18-year-old Croatian Janica Kostelic, who suffered
a season-ending knee injury last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
