<HEADLINE> China's Agricultural Sector to Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China will improve its
agricultural services, basic production conditions and
environmental protection in 2000, said the Chinese Minister of
Agriculture, Chen Yaobang today.
</P>
<P>
At the National Agricultural Work Conference which closed here
today, Chen pointed out that changes in the agricultural sector
will greatly improve agriculture production and lower production
costs, and will thus increase the income of Chinese farmers.
</P>
<P>
To attract more funds in the agriculture sector, China will
encourage investments from public and private sources as well as
foreign investment and technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
