<HEADLINE> Ministry of National Defense Hosts Reception </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- According to a senior official
with the Ministry of National Defense, 1999 was a fruitful year
for Chinese people,
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an evening reception marking the New Year, Luo Bin,
director of the Ministry's Foreign Affairs Office said that the
Chinese people jubilantly celebrated the 50th anniversary of the
People's Republic and the return of Macao last year.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Chi Haotian, who is also vice-chairman of
China's Central Military Commission and state councilor, attended
the reception along with a number of People's Liberation Army (PLA)
senior officials as well as various overseas military officers.
</P>
<P>
Luo said that in 1999 the PLA successfully carried out various
reforms including cutting back 500,000 of its armed forces staff
and performing successfully the Grand Military Parade for the 50th
anniversary celebrations in October last year.
</P>
<P>
The successful practice of "one country, two systems" in Hong
Kong and Macao will give impetus to an early settlement of the
Taiwan issue, said Luo. He added that the PLA is determined to
make new contributions for the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Luo said that in 2000 the PLA will continue to strive to
develop friendship and cooperative relations with its counterparts
across the world in line with the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
The PLA will continue to maintain world peace and do everything
in its power to improve mutual understanding, friendship, trust
and relations with armies around the world. said Luo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
