<HEADLINE> Thai Exporters to Explore Cambodia, Vietnam Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government is launching
new strategies to help Thai exporters expand to new markets,
particularly Cambodia and Vietnam, a senior commerce ministry
official said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Banpot Hongthong, director-general of the Department of Export
Promotion, was quoted by Thailand News Agency as saying that one
of the strategies the government employed to promote exports was
to send trade delegations to take part in trade fairs and
exhibitions held in targeted markets.
</P>
<P>
Thai trade delegations will visit Cambodia and Vietnam this
year to launch trade fairs there to promote Thai exports, he said.
</P>
<P>
The first Thai trade fair in Southeast Asia will be held in
Cambodia between March 3 and 5, followed by another one in Vietnam
between September 1 and 3, Banpot said.
</P>
<P>
Thai products to be demonstrated at the fairs will include food,
textiles and garments, furniture, leather products, automobile
parts, electrical appliances, electronic products, toys and
construction materials, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
