<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Arrests 4 Associates of Hijackers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Home Minister L K Advani
announced Thursday that four key associates of the five hijackers
of an Indian Airlines jet have been arrested in Mumbai.
</P>
<P>
The four, all Harkat-ul-Ansar operatives, are Mohd Rehan and
Mohd Iqbal (both Pakistani nationals), Yusuf Nepali (a Nepali
national) and Abdul Latif, an Indian.
</P>
<P>
The identity of the five hijackers has also been established
and they are all Pakistani nationals, Advani said.
</P>
<P>
The hijackers identified by these operatives are Ibrahim Athar
from Bahawalpur, Shahid Akhtar Sayed from Gulshan Iqbal of Karachi,
Sunny Ahmed Qazi from Defense Area of Karachi and Shaqir from
Sukkur City.
</P>
<P>
Advani said Athar is the brother of Maulana Masood Azhar, the
Pakistani cleric freed by India along with two other militants in
exchange for the hostages on the aircraft, which was hijacked on
Christmas Eve.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
