<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2,500 Rwanda Genocide Cases Settled in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- For the year 1999, 2,500 cases
of Rwanda genocide were settled, in which 116 people were
sentenced to death, judicial source has said.
</P>
<P>
The Rwanda News Agency quoted the source as saying that 322
people were sentenced to life imprisonment, 235 acquitted and more
than 425 sentenced to different years of imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The number of cases that were settled increased compared to the
past two years in which only 1,200 cases were settled.
</P>
<P>
However, Rwandan Minister of Justice Jean de Dieu Mucyo said
Wednesday that "the performance of the judicial sector is yet to
improve if the Gacaca courts (participatory justice) begin to
function."
</P>
<P>
The Gacaca Court (participatory justice) is a proposed judicial
system intended to speed up trial of genocide suspects since a big
number is so far detained in prisons and many more are not yet
arrested.
</P>
<P>
If these courts start functioning, the truth about the genocide
tragedy will be revealed and the culture of impunity will be
evicted so that unity and reconciliation will be attained.
</P>
<P>
A bill on Gacaca courts is now awaiting the Cabinet decision
after which, it will be submitted to parliament for adoption .
</P>
<P>
The justice minister expected the bill to begin functioning in
April this year.
</P>
<P>
There will be over 10,000 Gacaca courts throughout the country
with a comparatively bigger number of judges to try more than
125,000 suspects already detained and many more who are yet to be
arrested on charges of genocide and other crimes against humanity.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> American Golfer Ready to Defend Malaysian Open Title  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 6 (Xinhua) -- American Gerry Norquist
attempts to become the second player to win the Malaysian Open
Golf Championship title for the third time in the tournament's 39-
year history, according to the Asian Professional Golfers
Association (PGA) Thurday.
</P>
<P>
The 37-year-old Norquist confirmed that he would defend the 825,
000 U.S. dollar championship title at the scenic Templer Park
Country Club from February 10 to 13, the PGA said in a statement
issued here.
</P>
<P>
Norquist was quoted as saying in the statement "I'm delighted
to come back to defend my title as the Malaysian Open has a
special place in my heart. Whenever I'm in Malaysia, I feel very
comfortable. The fans are always encouraging me on the golf course
and I'm looking forward to coming back. I've only missed playing
the event once in 1997 when I suffered a broken rib."
</P>
<P>
Norquist, who has five Asian PGA titles to his credit, won his
second Malaysian Open triumph last year following his first win in
1993.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian Open is the season's opener for the 2000 Asian
PGA circuit and is the sixth event on the European Tour.
</P>
<P>
This year's Malaysian Open will be co-sponsored by the Asian
PGA and the European tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
