<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Spring Season Transport Starts on January 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China's annual railway
transportation peak season which sees tens of millions of people
travel across the country to return home for the traditional
Spring Festival will start on January 21 and end February 29, the
Ministry of Railways said today.
</P>
<P>
The "Spring Season Transport", as it is called, includes
transient laborers and college students returning home during
their winter vacation.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, more and more people have traveled during the
Spring Festival period. According to sociologists, the "sea of
humanity" that traverse the country during this period is due to
economic development and improved living conditions.
</P>
<P>
Due to the large amount of human traffic during this period,
China's transport system, chiefly the railway sector, works
especially hard to ensure that "traffic" runs smoothly.
</P>
<P>
A ministry official predicted that during the 40-day peak
season, the railway sector will have to handle 128 million
passengers, averaging 3.22 million per day. The estimated total
volume will be five percent more than last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
To ensure that transport services run on time, additional
passenger trains will be running. Ticket prices will also vary
depending on demand in an attempt to control the amount of human
traffic during the festive season.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0156 </DOCNO>
