Ma'ariv:
</P>
<P>
-- More than 100 people were evacuated in the Tel Aviv-Jaffa
area on Wednesday after heavy rain caused extensive flooding. Over
140 millimeters of rainfall was recorded in the Tel Aviv area from
Tuesday morning to Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Yediot Aharonot:
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli President Ezer Weizman told reporters Wednesday that
there are certain difficulties with turning over to the state
attorney the files requested for examination about the accusation
that he had received large sums of cash gifts from a French
millionaire.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to take about two weeks for Weizman's attorney
Ya'acov Weinroth to collect all the material. He attributed the
delay to the disappearance of files from the office of Weizman's
original lawyer, Hanina Brandes, who administered the cash account
in Weizman's name. 
