<HEADLINE> 2 People Killed in Plane Crash in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A Skypower Express Airways plane
crashlanded in Nigerian capital Abuja Wednesday, killing a
passenger and a farmer on the ground, The Guardian newspaper
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the airline confirmed the accident,
saying that a female passenger died in the accident while one
other occupant was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
The farmer died when the plane crashed into his farm, about 900
meters to the center line of the Abuja airport.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the aircraft was on a charter flight
from commercial hub Lagos to Ilorin, Minna and Abuja with eight
passengers and two crew on board.
</P>
<P>
The pilot of the aircraft reportedly radioed a distress call to
the airport, complaining of fire burning somewhere around the
aircraft cockpit.
</P>
<P>
Skypower management was "surprised and confused" as to the
cause of the accident because the aircraft recently underwent a
maintenance check, according to the airline's public relations
consultant Lateef Lawal.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the accident investigation bureau of the Federal
Ministry of Aviation, and the Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority
are already in Abuja to carry out preliminary investigations.
</P>
<P>
With Wednesday's mishap, Skypower has a record of an average of
one crash per year except for last year which was accident-free.
</P>
</TEXT>
