<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Turkish newspapers on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- A new protocol to improve management in Turkish prisons will
be put into force in the next few days.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocol, drawn jointly by Turkish Ministry of
Internal Affairs, Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Health and
General Command of Gendarme, the security, administration,
personnel training and electronic systems will be reviewed and
enhanced in order to solve prison chaos from the administrative
roots.
</P>
<P>
Riots of prisoners have taken place in Turkey frequently in
recent years because of crowded wards and administration flaw.
