<HEADLINE> Estrada May Announce Cabinet Changes on Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada said Thursday that he is likely to announce changes in his
cabinet on Saturday, when he delivers his Report to the Nation
from the Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released from the Presidential Palace, Estrada
said he would continue to study his options on who among the
members of his cabinet shall be fired, retained or reassigned
</P>
<P>
"I've to study my options well. I'll announce my decision soon.
I will make sure that my decision will benefit the nation," he
said.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, he added, he is likely to announce his decision on
the fate of some cabinet members, along with their respective
replacements.
</P>
<P>
Estrada also said he felt sad over the resignation of Edgardo
Espiritu as secretary of the Department of Finance, saying
Espiritu did much to help his administration.
</P>
<P>
He lauded Espiritu for bringing down interest rates, restoring
a sense of fiscal discipline and responsibility, adding that he
would be willing to give Espiritu another post in the government.
</P>
<P>
"But his resignation is irrevocable, and he cited family
reasons. He has also neglected his personal business just to join
my team," he said.
</P>
<P>
Espiritu submitted to Estrada his "irrevocable" resignation
during a meeting in the Presidential Palace on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Espiritu said in his letter that his one-and-a-half year stay
in government was "undoubtedly very gratifying" as he helped
improve the country's economy and the Filipinos' plight. 
</P>
