<HEADLINE> Kenyan Ambassador Burgled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Ambassador to the United
States Samson Chemai was burgled Wednesday in the Kenyan capital
Nairobi by six thugs with AK 47 rifles and pistols.
</P>
<P>
The ordeal began at 3:00 a.m. local time and lasted for five
hours, the East African Standard daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The robbers forced Chemai, his two daughters and his
granddaughter into one place and threatened to shoot them if they
did not give all the money they had, the ambassador was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The gang looted 6,000 shillings (about 80 U.S. dollars), a
television set, a fax machine, four speakers, a pair of sports
shoes and other assorted household goods.
</P>
<P>
Because the thugs could not drive, they forced the ambassador
to drive them in his Mercedes Benz around the city. The ambassador
was eventually dumped in the suburb with his vehicle.
</P>
<P>
Chemai drove directly to a police station at about 8:00 a.m.
and the police rushed to the scene and recovered four speakers and
a fax machine hidden in a maize plantation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
