<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20 Percent of School Children HIV Positive in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The AIDS virus is mowing down
school- going children in Kenya and currently more than 20 percent
of the pupils within the age group of 14 - 7 are HIV positive.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Education Minister Kalonzo Musyoka Wednesday released
the shocking statistics when he launched this year's national
schools Form One selection at the Kenya Science Teachers College
in the capital Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
"The scourge threatens all gains made in the education sector
and stall any meaningful progress achieved so far," the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the killer disease is also a serious threat to teachers
as many of them are dying of AIDS.
</P>
<P>
At national level, he said, approximately 1.9 million Kenyans
are infected with the killer virus, with two thirds of them under
the age of 25.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Ministry of Health indicate that about 500
Kenyans die of AIDS every day.
</P>
<P>
Last November, Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi declared AIDS a
national disaster due to its heavy toll on Kenyans.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the country has put the syllabuses for AIDS
lessons in place, requiring teachers in various subjects to
address the scourge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
