<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya's Coffee Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 6 (xinhua) -- Kenya's coffee production last
year is estimated at around 67,000 tons compared with 55,000 tons
in the previous year, according to the Coffee Board of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The coffee board attributed the output increase to favorable
growing conditions in the country, according to a report by the
East African Standard newspaper on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It is projected that the coffee output for the 1999/2000 will
be around 80,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The coffee board noted that Kenya will be carrying out
fortnightly coffee auctions this month due to coffee delivery
affected by the public holidays in December, and will return to
weekly auctions in February.
</P>
<P>
The Nairobi Coffee Exchange held its first sale for the new
year Tuesday, offering 32,333 60-kilogram bags of coffee against
45,000 bags sold on December 15.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the exchange said they will offer 35,000 to 40,000
 bags of coffee in the next auction scheduled for January 25.
</P>
</TEXT>
