<HEADLINE> Seven Angolan Rebels Killed in Namibia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Seven Angolan rebels have been
killed and four others became prisoners of war during a combat
against the Namibian government troops in the Namibian north
border area close to Angola, official source said here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The conflict between the Namibian Armed Forces and the members
of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA)
occurred on Wednesday near the village of Kongola, some 400
kilometers east to the Namibian border city of Rundu.
</P>
<P>
Namibian Chief of the General Staff Martin Shalli said his
troops are determined to combat against the invaders until the
last Savimbist is expelled out of the Namibian territory.
</P>
<P>
Shalli accused the Savimbist terrorists of launching an ambush
against civilian vehicles on January 3 near the northeastern
Namibian village of Bagani, during which three French children
were killed while their parents and two members of humanitarian
organizations were injured.
</P>
<P>
According to official source, the Namibian government has
authorized the Angolan government troops to enter into the
Namibian territory for pursuing the rebels hiding in Namibia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
