<HEADLINE> 92 Illegal Immigrants Arrested in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A total of 92 illegal immigrants
were arrested in Zambia last month, Times of Zambia newspaper
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper quoted public relations officer of the
immigration department Denny Lungu as saying here that on December
17, immigrations officers raided a house in Chawama township in
Lusaka where a Congolese deportee was picked up.
</P>
<P>
A search in the house yielded passports of various
nationalities, identity cards of different countries, blank
immigration documents, rubber stamps and other materials used in
forgery of documents.
</P>
<P>
The Congolese is currently appearing in court for breaking the
deportation order and being in possession of items believed to be
stolen for illegally making documents.
</P>
<P>
The department has meanwhile warned the public to resist
temptations by illegal immigrants to obtain or alter documents.
</P>
