<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Plunging in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices continued plunging in
Tokyo Thursday, dragged down by information and technology issues
which faced selling following their recent sharp gains.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, which lost 460.31 points on
Wednesday, fell another 374.28 points, or 2.02 percent, to close
at the day's low of 18,168.27.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, tumbled 42.25 points or 2.56 percent to 1,
609.59.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section went up to 574.24 million shares
from Wednesday's 553.10 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Sega Enterprises, a major maker of video game consoles, was the
day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented high-tech issues were hit by Wednesday's fall
in the technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index in New York, while
information and telecommunication issues also remained under
selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the biggest winners were drug makers surging 9.80
percent as a sector.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers surpassed
gainers 771 to 432, while 140 issues ended unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
