<HEADLINE> Top Seed Beaten in Auckland Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AUCKLAND, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Elena Likhovtseva of
Russia was toppled by Cara Black of Zimbabwe in the quarterfinal
of the New Zealand Women's Tennis Classic here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The African rising star, the sixth seed in the tournament,
advanced to the last four with a 6-3, 7-5 win.
</P>
<P>
Likhovtseva who ranked 18th in the world, became the victim of
a lengthy second round match against Slovenia's Katrina Srebotnik
on Wednesday, followed by a three-set doubles match.
</P>
<P>
"I was tired from yesterday, I played six sets, I was still
sore going out onto court today," said the Russian who
acknowledged that Black also played an error-free match.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Black who won the junior Wimbledon and US Open
titles in 1997, increased her head-to-head record against
Likhovtseva to 2-1.
</P>
<P>
In other quarterfinal matches, American Meghann Shaughnessy
beat fifth-seed Anna Smashnova of Israel 6-4, 6-2, and second-seed
Anne Kremer of Luxembourg sailed further over Argentina's Paola
Suarez 6-3, 5-7, 6-4. 
</P>
