<HEADLINE> Northern China Airport Reopens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Xiantao Airport in Shenyang,
capital city of northeast China's Liaoning Province, reopened this
morning after being closed for 12 hours due to snow and icy
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The first flight took off at 10:00 a.m., airport sources said,
adding that workers are trying their best to reduce economic
losses.
</P>
<P>
Heavy snow hit Shenyang and neighboring areas in the last two
days, forcing Xiantao Airport to close for several times. At least
16 flights were delayed.
</P>
<P>
Snow also has affected most parts of northern China. In Beijing
alone, expressways leading to other cities in the region also were
closed early this week, with more than 1,600 minor accidents
reported, but no injuries.  
</P>
