<HEADLINE> Thailand Keeps Giant-Killing Spree at Hopman Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Thailand continued its giant-
killing spree by beating former title-holders Slovakia in the
Hopman Cup mixed teams tennis tournament in Perth on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Thais have achieved an unbeatable 2-0 lead as both Tamarine
Tanasugarn and Paradorn Srichaphan won their singles clashes over
Slovak, winners of the contest two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Tanasugarn outwitted her opponent Henrieta Nagyova 2-6, 6-2, 6-
1 before 106th-ranked Paradorn Srichaphan caused the biggest upset
by conquering 17th-ranked Karol Kucera 4-6, 7-6 (7/2), 6-2 in the
men's singles.
</P>
<P>
Thailand becomes the first team in Group B to gain two wins,
and will surely make the final if it beats Austria on Friday in
its last clash of the qualifying round robin.
</P>
<P>
American-born Tanasugarn, 22, registered her third successive
singles win although she was ranked a humble 72nd in the world as
Nagyova surrendered at 4-1 in the final set due to thigh strain.
</P>
<P>
She also played a big part in Thailand's 2-1 win over Japan
last Saturday when she beat Ai Sugiyama to pace the Thais for the
main draw of the competition.
</P>
<P>
She performed superbly on Tuesday to beat Australia's 16-year-
old wonder player Jelena Dokic, a crucial part of Thailand's 2-1
victory over the reigning champions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
