<HEADLINE> '99 Kunming Horticulture Expo Sets 8 Guinness Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The '99 Kunming World
Horticulture Expo set eight world records confirmed recently by
the Shanghai Office of the Guinness Book of World Records.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, held in Kunming, capital of southwest China's
Yunnan Province, from May 1 to October 31 last year, received over
9 million visitors.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, the largest of its kind ever held in China,
attracted participants from 95 countries and international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,511 varieties of trees and plants from around the world
were displayed at the expo gardens which covered an area of 218
hectares. 
