<HEADLINE> China Issues First Public Welfare Postcards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A set of three postcards has
been issued in Shanghai to raise fund to help needy people.
</P>
<P>
This is China's first set of postcards released for this
purpose since 1949.
</P>
<P>
The postcards were jointly designed by the Shanghai Municipal
Post Bureau and the Shanghai Charity Foundation, and a total of
150,000 sets will be put into circulation.
</P>
<P>
All proceeds from the issue will be used by the charity
foundation to aid the handicapped and other needy people in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Charity Foundation has received some 200 million
yuan worth of donations since it was founded in 1994.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, the foundation has helped more than 160
orphaned children find a home with local families, and enabled
some 7,500 poor students to continue their education.  
</P>
