<HEADLINE> China's First Tax Payer of Year 2000 Found in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Xu Shunbo, a self-employed
worker in China's oldest special economic zone of Shenzhen in
Guangdong Province has become the country's first tax payer in the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Xu handed in 53 yuan in turnover tax through an automatic tax
declaration outlet at the local taxation bureau at 00:53 on the
first day of the New Year. The computer system in the State
Administration of Taxation confirmed that Xu was the first to pay
taxes in China in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Now, 60 percent of the tax payers in Shenzhen pay their taxes
through automatic outlets that operate around-the-clock. This
network system remained free of the Y2K bug, and in the first two
days of the year the city was able to put more than 210,000 yuan
into its tax coffer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
