<HEADLINE> China Uncovers Cigarette Smuggling Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese customs officers have
recently seized four containers of smuggled cigarettes worth 14.57
million yuan (about 1.67 million US. dollars) in the northeastern
port city of Yingkou.
</P>
<P>
The containers were packed with "555," "Mild Seven," and other
brands of foreign cigarettes when they were seized at the city's
Bayuquan harbor on January 3, according to Dalian Customs
officials.
</P>
<P>
The smugglers attempted to evade taxes amounting to 7.02
million yuan, the officers said.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Customs cracked this case successfully after three
months of investigation.  
</P>
