<HEADLINE> Payton Paces Sonics to Beat Spurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Gary Payton had 24 points, 10
assists and six rebounds as the Seattle SuperSonics knocked NBA
champion San Antonio Spurs out of first place with a 99-96 away
victory on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Payton made a clutch jumper with 19 seconds to play, giving the
SuperSonics a 97-91 lead and eventual victory, which dragged the
Spurs one-half game behind Utah for the top spot in the Midwest
Division.
</P>
<P>
Tim Duncan had 24 points and 12 rebounds and David Robinson
added 20 and 11 for San Antonio (21-12), which has dropped five of
its last eight games.
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone scored 30 points as the Utah Jazz recorded their
best offensive output of the season and coasted to a 118-96 home
victory over the Charlotte Hornets who have lost six of their last
seven.
</P>
<P>
The victory boosted the Jazz (20-10) past San Antonio and into
first place in the Midwest.
</P>
<P>
In Los Angeles, the Lakers swept the Clippers as Shaquille O'
Neal scored 40 points and pulled down 19 rebounds for a 118-101
win.
</P>
<P>
Kobe Bryant added 26 points for the Lakers (27-5), who extended
their winning streak to 12 games.
</P>
<P>
The lowly Chicago Bulls welcomed Toni Kukoc back to their
lineup after 24 games due to a back injury, and the versatile
forward scored 18 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to snap the Bulls
' 11-game losing skid with a 77-66 win over the Washington Wizards.
</P>
<P>
Yet, nothing comes easy for Chicago (3-26), which nearly blew a
14-point lead entering the fourth quarter as Washington scored the
first 11 points of the final period to cut the deficit to 66-63
with 8:16 remaining.
</P>
<P>
Elton Brand had 16 points and 16 boards for Chicago, Tracy
Murray had 18 points off the bench for the Wizards.
</P>
<P>
In Philadelphia, Allen Iverson led the 76ers with 34 points and
Matt Geiger contributed a season-high 26 to lead Philadelphia to a
113-92 win over the Golden State Warriors.
</P>
<P>
In Atlanta, Grant Hill scored a season-high 42 points for the
second straight game as the streaking Detroit Pistons shot down
the Hawks 120-108.
</P>
<P>
In Orlando, Chris Gatling scored 23 points off the bench as the
Magic snapped a five-game losing streak by beating the Vancouver
Grizzlies 116-96. 
</P>
</TEXT>
