<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Rice Exports Hit New High in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Thailand exported 6.658 million
tons of rice in 1999, the highest level in the country's export
history,Somboon Pathaichan, manager of the Rice Exporters'
Association, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The figure makes Thailand remain the world's largest rice
exporter.The country exported 6.367 million tons of rice with a
total value of 85 billion baht (2.29 billion U.S. dollar) in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Somboon told Xinhua that the association is still collecting
the export value, which will be lower than last year because of
the exchange rate factor.
</P>
<P>
The Thai baht was trade at as low as 50 baht to the dollar in
1998 compared to 36 baht in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Somboon expected Thailand's rice export volume to be at around
6 million tons this year, slightly lower than that of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Paddy production are expected to reach 18.9 million tons in
2000,compared to 18.2 million tons in 1999, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that export prices are expected to decline on the
estimated worldwide production of 500 million tons of rice this
year compared to a global demand of 22 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
