<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Panama rejected the entrance
of two American grape containers suspected of contamination with a
plague called Pseudococcus Cochinneal, the local press reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted an official from the Fishing and Farming
Ministry (MIDA) as saying that the samples of grapes taken from
the two containers, which belong to an American fruit firm, carry
the plague which could affect coffee, mango and citric fruits.
</P>
<P>
The official said that vegetable sanitary officials from MIDA,
fishing and farming quarantine in Puerto de Manzanillo and
agricultural specialists of the American Embassy in Panama,
participated in the collection of the samples. 
