<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pinochet Carries Out Medical Examination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Chile's ex-military leader,
Augusto Pinochet, underwent Wednesday a medical examination in a
London hospital, according to reports reaching here from London.
</P>
<P>
British Home Secretary Jack Straw will decide, according to
results of the medical examination, if he authorizes the
extradition of Pinochet to Spain or concedes him liberty on
humanitarian grounds, the reports say.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, 84 years old, was examined by three British geriatric,
neurology and diabetes specialists at Northwick Park Hospital of
Harrow, in north London. The ex-military leader and current life-
long senator now suffers from about twenty illnesses, including
diabetes and heart problems.
</P>
<P>
Personnel from Chile's embassy in London accompanied Pinochet
to hospital. The appeal hearing regarding Pinochet's delivery to
Spain is planned for March 20 in London's High Court.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was detained on October 16, 1998 in London at request
of a Spanish judge who intends to bring him to trial for crimes
against humanity occurring in Chile during the military regime,
from 1973 to 1990. Last October, a British judge authorized
Pinochet's extradition to Spain. However, the definite decision
will be taken by Straw 15 or 20 days after he receives the medical
report.
</P>
<P>
Supporters of Pinochet displayed fear that the military ex-
leader won't resist judgment in Spain and will die. The Chilean
government requested Straw the freeing of Pinochet under
humanitarian grounds owing to his old age and deteriorated state
of health. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
