Committee said that the country's two-way trade from January to
October was 15.07 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports totaled 6.85
billion dollars and imports 8.22 billion dollars, dropping by 1
percent and 15.4 percent respectively. (Romania-Foreign Trade)
