<HEADLINE> S. Lankan PM Calls for Destruction of Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Prime Minister
Sirimavo Bandaranaike has called for destruction of menace of
terrorism which had taken the lives of thousands of innocent
public servants and civilians in the country.
</P>
<P>
A suicide bomb attacked outside the prime minister office
Wednesday morning, killing 13 people and injuring 24 others.
However, the prime minister was not in the office at that time.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Wednesday night, she extended her deepest
sympathies to the families of the dead and wished all those who
were injured a speedy recovery.
</P>
<P>
She said it is indeed a great tragedy that some personnel
attached to her office were brutally killed when a woman terrorist
bomber exploded herself.
</P>
<P>
"While the menace of terrorism which killed thousands of
civilians should be condemned, you will all realize that the time
has now come for us to collectively get together for the total
eradication of controlled terrorism," she added. 
</P>
