<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Corinthians Beats Raja Casablanca 2-0 in World Club Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Corinthians beat
African champions Raja Casablanca 2-0 in the World Club Soccer
Championship in Sao Paulo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Luizao of the Corinthians team opened the scoring in the 50th
minute and his teammate Fabio Luciano fired a shot against the
Raja crossbar following a goalmouth scramble in the 68th minute.
</P>
<P>
The ball bounced down and was cleared by a Moroccan defender
but referee Stefano Braschi ruled that it had crossed the line and
awarded a goal.
</P>
<P>
But television replays showed that the ball did not go over the
line.
</P>
<P>
Raja played plenty of neat football, created several good
chances but were let down by their failure to get in enough shots
on goal.
</P>
<P>
Corinthians were superbly marshalled by Colombian captain
Freddy Rincon but were otherwise unimpressive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
