<HEADLINE> Largest Bromide Plant for East Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Israeli bromide company,
the largest of its kind in China, has been set up in the city of
Weifang in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Weifang Sino-Israeli Bromide Company Ltd. will produce
eight kinds of bromides involving high technology and high added
value, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project involves an investment of 30
million US dollars, and each side will hold 50 percent of the
shares.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture's annual sales income is expected to reach 43
million US dollars, said Du Defu, chairman of the Haihua Group.
Haihua, the Chinese investor in the project, is China's largest
production base for oceanic chemicals.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the joint venture may reach 300 million US
dollars in the future, Du said. 
</P>
