<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Japan Bilateral Trade Drops Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The bilateral trade between
Myanmar and Japan was 247.92 million U.S. dollars in the first
eight months of 1999, down 1.57 percent from the same period of
1998.
</P>
<P>
The official Economic Indicators said in its latest issue that
Myanmar's import from Japan was valued at 209.6 million dollars, 8.
5 percent less than the 229.1 million dollars in the corresponding
period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar's export to Japan in the period stood at 38.
32 million dollars, increasing by 68 percent over the same period
of 1998 .
</P>
<P>
During the period from April 1994 to July 1999, Myanmar
absorbed investment amounting to 123 million dollars from Japan,
which accounted for 2.18 percent of the total foreign investment
flowing into Myanmar during the period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
