<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Fish, Prawn Exports Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar exported 29,700 tons of
fish and prawn in the first eight months of 1999, a 22.25 percent
drop from the same period of 1998 which was 38,200 tons.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, fish accounted for 22,900 tons and prawn 6,800
tons, according to the latest figures released by the country's
Central Statistical Organization.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, export earnings of fish and prawn in the eight-month
period totaled 73.51 million U.S. dollars, 29.74 percent less than
that obtained in the corresponding period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar annually produces over 910,000 tons of fish and prawn,
of which over 240,000 tons are fresh water fish and prawn, and
over 670,000 tons are deep sea fish and prawn.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, in 1998, Myanmar's export of fish
and prawn totaled 62,400 tons with an earning of 159.38 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since Myanmar adopted the open-door economic policy in late
1988, foreign investment in the fishery sector has reached 197
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
