<HEADLINE> Int'l Loan Program Helps Chinese Women Find Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Sixty Chinese women who lost
their jobs have found new hope again thanks to the aid of an
international program.
</P>
<P>
 The United Nations Development Program and the Australian
Agency for International Development, in cooperation with the
Chinese government, will provide loans for the laid-off workers to
receive professional training for new employment.
</P>
<P>
 The women, in the port city of Tianjin in north China, will
learn the skills needed to work in restaurants, retail sales, the
processing industry, gardening, and entertainment centers. They
began their training courses last week.
</P>
<P>
 The 60 women are the first group to benefit from the program,
which will help thousands of laid-off women workers in the city
with loans amounting to 900,000 U.S. dollars over three years.
</P>
<P>
 This is the first time China has utilized international loans
to help laid-off women workers in cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
