<HEADLINE> Fowler Told Another Operation Might not Needed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer
club Liverpool striker Robbie Fowler was told on Wednesday that
second operation may not be needed on his troublesome ankle.
</P>
<P>
The England forward underwent a third scan on Tuesday as
Liverpool's medical team attempted to find a reason for the
discomfort in the ankle joint.
</P>
<P>
Fowler has been complaining of pain when running since an
operation in October to remove a spur from the bone.
</P>
<P>
There were fears the striker may have needed more surgery to
correct the problem but Liverpool's French manager Gerard Houllier
confirmed Fowler was simply told to rest the ankle for three weeks
before continuing his comeback.
</P>
<P>
Houllier said on Wednesday: "The doctor is adamant the problem
will not need another operation and we hope the rest will help."
