<HEADLINE> Thatcher Charged by FA  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon defender Ben Thatcher
was charged by the Football Association with misconduct after the
game against Sunderland on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The FA deemed video evidence to be necessary after Thatcher was
seen elbowing Sunderland winger Nicky Summerbee during Monday's
clash at Selhurst Park.
</P>
<P>
FA spokesman Adrian Bevington said: "We requested a video of
the game on Tuesday morning and have charged Ben Thatcher with
misconduct."
</P>
<P>
The incident led to Carl Cort's winner in the game but was
missed by referee Graham Poll.
</P>
<P>
Thatcher was apologetic after the incident but insisted the
challenge was accidental and said: "I was running flat out for a
50/50 ball.
</P>
<P>
"He pulled out of the challenge after I'd already braced myself
for contact. If my elbow caught him I apologize. It was certainly
unintentional."
</P>
<P>
Thatcher now has 14 days to respond to the charge. 
</P>
