<HEADLINE> Pele Voted Player of Century  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Pele has been voted player of the
20th century ahead of Dutch star Johan Cruyff and inspirational
German Franz Beckenbauer.
</P>
<P>
A poll conducted by the International Federation of Football
History and Statistics awarded Brazilian legend Pele 1,705 points,
while Cruyff polled 1,303 and Beckenbauer 1,228.
</P>
<P>
Cruyff said: "I think the poll has the right winner. Surely it
was decisive that Pele won three World Cup titles."
</P>
<P>
Alfredo di Stefano took fourth place followed by such greats as
Diego Maradona, Ferenc Puskas, Michel Platini, Garrincha, Eusebio
and Bobby Charlton.
</P>
<P>
Lev Yashin, the late Russian giant, was voted top goalkeeper of
the century, followed by Gordon Banks of England and Dino Zoff of
Italy.
</P>
<P>
Jose Luis Chilavert of Paraguay and Peter Schmeichel of Denmark
were the only two players still playing to make it onto either
list.
</P>
<P>
Schmeichel and Chilavert were beaten by Germany's Oliver Kahn
to be proclaimed top world goalkeeper in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Wanderley Luxemburgo of Brazil was named top national team
coach of 1999, the top club coach was Manchester United's Alex
Ferguson and the top referee Pierluigi Collina of Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
