<HEADLINE> Maradona Tests Positive for Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Jan 5 (Xinhua) -- Hospitalized Argentine
soccer star Diego Maradona has tested positive fro cocaine with
his blood and urine samples after he checked into a Uruguayan
hospital with blood pressure and heart problem, a chief police
officers said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"I have been authorized by a judge to inform you that our test
(blood and urine) has resulted positive for cocaine," Maximo Costa
Rocha, police chief for the Uruguayan province of Maldonado, told
a news conference.
</P>
<P>
Maradona was admitted to the intensive care unit of a hospital
in the Uruguayan resort town of Punta del Este on Tuesday
suffering from what his doctor called hypertension and an
irregular heartbeat.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old soccer star who led Argentina to victory in the
1986 World Cup final against Germany has a long history of drug
abuse.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rocha said Maradona had not been arrested but that
investigations were continuing. A second drug test was being
analysed, he said. 
</P>
