<HEADLINE> Two Top Players Beaten in Australian Women's Hardcourt Championships  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The French top seed collapsed 6-0, 6-1 to in-form Bulgarian
Magdalena Maleeva.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Kournikova was rolled in three sets by Croatia'
s top player, seventh-seeded Silvija Talaja, in the packed 1500-
seat stadium at Royal Pines Resort.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova took the first set 6-4 Wednesday, winning the last
five games after being down 4-0.
</P>
