Talaja 6-4 in just over half an hour.
</P>
<P>
The Russian then gave away a 2-1 lead in the final set to let
the 21-year-old Croatian cruise home 6-2 -- an unforced error, a
shot wide of the baseline, delivering the final nail in her coffin
as she served to stay in the match.
</P>
<P>
In the four years since turning professional, the Russian has
been a finalist twice, semi-finalist seven times and, after
Wednesday's capitulation, a quarter-finalist eight times.
</P>
<P>
And the prospects for her Australian summer are not bright with
the field at next week's tournament in Sydney featuring three of
the world's top 10.
