<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0312 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Has Surplus Rice in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia is expected to have
a surplus of 144,000 tons of rice in the 1999-2000 fiscal year,
the largest for several years, the Evening News said Wednesday,
quoting the Agriculture Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's paddy production for the wet and dry seasons during
the 1999-2000 fiscal year is estimated at more than 3 million tons
which can produce 1.96 million tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
The unit paddy production averaged 1.65 tons per hectare in
Cambodia. With its 11.4 million people needing a total of 1.8
million tons of rice per year, Cambodia will have a surplus of 144,
000 tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia cultivated about 1.89 million hectares of paddies in
1999, 135,000 hectares more than in 1998. Of the total, about 20,
000 hectares of paddies were hit by flood or insects.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's wet season lasts from May to November every year
while the dry season comes between December and April.
</P>
<P>
The good harvest is attributed to adequate rainfall and the
extension of cropping areas as well as the minimal damage from
flooding, drought and insects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
