<HEADLINE> Denmark Grants Aid to Nepal for Better Media Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Danish government has
agreed to provide a grant assistance of 80 million rupees (1.15
million U.S. dollars) to Nepal to increase professionalism of the
free media and improve access to relevant media technologies in
the country.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the Danish Embassy here
Wednesday, the grant will include support to the Nepal Press
Institute in training activities and to regional media resource
centers in its capacity building.
</P>
<P>
The assistance will also go to the Nepal Press Council for the
expansion of a media development fund aimed at facilitating
investments by independent media in Nepal, the release said.
