Putin on Thursday signed a decree amending the country's national
security concept to define terrorism and organized crime as of a
political rather than merely criminal nature.
</P>
<P>
The 21-page amendment more clearly "defines the notion of a
multi-polar world" and makes proposals on ways to combat terrorism
and organized crime, the Itar-Tass news agency reported, quoting
Sergei Ivanov, secretary of the Russian Security Council, a top
advisory body.
</P>
