<DOCNO> XIE20000106.0338 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2200GMT, Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein on Thursday said that
the United Nations embargo imposed on Iraq "has actually started"
to be corroded "thanks to the great fortitude and the endurance of
the Iraqi people."
</P>
<P>
Saddam made the remarks in a nationally televised address to
mark the 79th anniversary of the founding of the Iraqi National
Army.
</P>
<P>
He said "we have said it with certainty that the embargo will
not be lifted by a (U.N.) Security Council resolution, but will
corrode by itself."
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov said here
Thursday that Moscow plans to host a multi-national Middle East
peace conference next month, the first in more than three years.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, who is accompanying former Russian President Boris
Yeltsin on a three-day visit to the Holy Land to mark the first
Orthodox Christmas of the new millennium, said the conference would
be held at the level of foreign ministers.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported that a spokesman in the Israeli Foreign
Ministry confirmed the Russian plan. This may mark a comeback of
Russia to the stage of mideast peace-making - the former Soviet
Union was a co-sponsor of the mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The second-phase troop redeployment by Israel
Defense Force (IDF) on the West Bank are proceeding smoothly and
will be completed on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The IDF has already evacuated six military bases as part of the
troop withdrawal and two of them, Camp Yosef near the northern West
Bank city of Nablus and Camp Barak near Jenin, are now in the hands
of the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The IDF soldiers and the Palestinian security forces started
Thursday conducting joint patrols in the areas just transferred to
the Palestinians in the vicinities of Jenin, Ramallah and Hebron,
the IDF spokesman's office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Bahraini Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Isa Al-Khalifa
arrived in the Qatari capital of Doha Thursday to further the
recently improved ties between the two Gulf Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The Bahraini Emir's brief visit came nine days after Qatar's
Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa Al-Thani's tour of Bahrain on
December 28, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The two emirs agreed in the Bahraini capital of Manama to
exchange ambassadors and to set up a joint committee to try to
settle a border dispute through cordial means. 
</P>
</TEXT>
