<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt, UAE Active in Convening Pan-Arab Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on
Thursday received a message from UAE President Sheikh Zayed Bin
Sultan Al-Nahyan on bilateral relations and ongoing efforts toward
the convening of an pan-Arab summit.
</P>
<P>
The message was brought to Mubarak by visiting UAE Minister of
State for Foreign Affairs Sheikh Hamdan Bin Zayed Al-Nahyan at the
red sea resort in Sharm el Sheikh.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Zayed strongly believes in the importance of holding a
comprehensive Arab summit to restore inter-Arab solidarity to
improve its standing on the regional and global fronts, Sheikh
Hamdan told the press.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders totally agree on the necessity to hold such a
summit that is to unify Arab ranks, mend the split within the Arab
countries and result in a unified position that will strengthen the
just and comprehensive peace process on the Palestinian, Syrian and
Lebanese tracks according to international law and the principle of
land for peace, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the summit will begin with a meeting of foreign
ministers who will study all pending issues and respectively set
the summit's agenda, he added.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamdan left Sharm el Sheikh after meeting with Mubarak.
</P>
</TEXT>
