<HEADLINE> Hizbullah Behind Kidnapping of Businessmen in Istanbul: Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Istanbul police claimed that
Hezbollah, a radical Islamist organization, was involved in the
kidnapping of three leading Turkish businessmen who disappeared
since the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Hizbullah was behind the incident, which rose the number of
businessmen who have been kidnapped in Istanbul in the last four
months to nine, the Turkish Daily News reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The alleged kidnapping of the three men is linked to six others
who have been reported missing earlier, said the police.
</P>
<P>
Searches for the missing have been conducted in Istanbul and its
surrounding areas, especially farm houses.
</P>
<P>
The Hizbullah was accused of kidnapping a Turkish feminist
writer two years ago. The radical group reportedly carried out
assassinations against the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK)
and its sympathizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
