<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Customs Reports Increasing Drug Haul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Canada Customs seized at least
240 million U.S. dollars in drugs in 1999, from 193 million
dollars worth in 1998, the department reported here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Of the reported national 1999 drug haul, nearly a tonne of
contraband drugs worth 114.3 million dollars was nabbed at the
country's largest Pearson International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Pearson recorded a drug take of 90.3 million dollars in 1998.
The airport usually catches about 40 percent of the national total,
according to the customs statistics.
</P>
<P>
For last year's national tally, authorities grabbed 796
kilograms of cocaine valued at 110 million dollars and 361,805
doses of Ecstasy, which were worth 8.8 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
