<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank to Launch Electronic Bond Offerings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced
Thursday its intention to launch the first fully integrated global
electronic bond offerings -- to be offered, distributed, and
traded on-line.
</P>
<P>
The offerings is expected to be a minimum of 3 billion U.S.
dollars. Lead managers will be Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co., and Lehman
Brothers.
</P>
<P>
"We designed this first comprehensive, end-to-end global
Internet offering to set a new standard in the market in terms of
market reach, liquidity, and transparency," said Afsaneh
Mashayekhi Beschloss, Vice-President and Treasurer of the World
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank has been issuing debt securities in the
international capital markets for more than 50 years. The bank's
debt securities are the funding source for development loans and
have provided financing for more than 4,000 development projects
in 130 countries through 300 billion dollars in lending. 
</P>
</TEXT>
